<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-5833] Reset thread interrupt state in case of InterruptedException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5833</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are some places where InterruptedException is caught but thread interrupt state is not reset.&lt;br/&gt;
e.g. from WorkerSourceTask#execute() :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (InterruptedException e) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Ignore and allow to exit.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proper way of handling InterruptedException is to reset thread interrupt state.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
